n)\nBULLET::::- \"Dillinger in Hollywood\" (2004) (short story collection)\n\nBULLET::::- Bruce Springsteen – \"Born in the U.S.A.\"\nBULLET::::- Bruce Springsteen – \"I'm on Fire\"\nBULLET::::- Bruce Springsteen – \"Glory Days\"\n\nAwards for \"Honeydripper\":\nBULLET::::- Outstanding Independent or Foreign Film (Win) – 2008 NAACP Image Award\nBULLET::::- Outstanding Writing in a Motion Picture (Theatrical or Television) (Nominated) – John Sayles – 2008 NAACP Image Awards\nBULLET::::- Top 10 Independent Films of 2007 – National Board of Review of Motion Pictures\nBULLET::::- Best Screenplay (Win) – John Sayles – 2007 San Sebastián International Film Festival (Tied with Gracia Querejeta and David Planell for Siete mesas de billar francés (2007))\n\nAward for \"Silver City\":\nBULLET::::- Golden Seashell Award for Best Film (Nominated) – John Sayles – 2004 San Sebastián International Film Festival\n\nAwards for \"Sunshine State\":\nBULLET::::- Golden Orange Award (Win) – John Sayles – 2002 Florida Film Critics Circle Awards\nBULLET::::- Special Mention For Excellence In Filmmaking (Win) – 2002 National Board of Review\n\nAwards for \"Limbo\":\nBULLET::::- Best Director Golden Space Needle Award (Win) – John Sayles −1999 Seattle International Film Festival\nBULLET::::- Outstanding Indies (Win) – 1999 National Board of Review\n\nAwards for \"Men with Guns/Hombres armados\":\nBULLET::::- Best Foreign Independent Film (Nominated) – 1998 British Independent Film Awards\nBULLET::::- Best Foreign Film (Nominated) – 1999 Golden Globes\nBULLET::::- Peace Award (Nominated) – 1998 Political Film Society\nBULLET::::- FIPRESCI Prize (Win) – John Sayles – 1997 San Sebastián International Film Festival\nBULLET::::- OCIC Award (Win) – John Sayles – 1997 San Sebastián International Film Festival\nBULLET::::- Solidarity Award (Win) – John Sayles – 1997 San Sebastián International Film Festival\nBULLET::::- Golden Seashell Award for Best Film (Nominated) – John Sayles – 1997 San Sebastián International Film Festival\n\nAwards for \"Lone Star\":\nBULLET::::- Best Original Screenplay (Nominated) – John Sayles – 1997 Academy Awards\nBULLET::::- Best Original Screenplay (Nominated) – John Sayles – 1997 BAFTA Awards\nBULLET::::- Best Screenplay, Motion Picture (Nominated) – John Sayles – 1997 Golden Globes\nBULLET::::- Best Screenplay Written Directly for the Screen (Nominated) – John Sayles – 1997 Writers Guild of America Award\nBULLET::::- Best Picture (Nominated) – 1997 Broadcast Film Critics Association Awards\nBULLET::::- Best Motion Picture Original Screenplay (Win) – John Sayles – 1997 Golden Satellite Awards\nBULLET::::- Best Motion Picture – Drama (Nominated) – Maggie Renzi & R. Paul Miller – 1997 Golden Satellite Awards\nBULLET::::- Best Screenplay (Nominated) – John Sayles – 1997 Independent Spirit Awards\nBULLET::::- Best Film (Win) – Lone Star – 1996 Lone Star Film & Television Awards\nBULLET::::- Best Director (Win) – John Sayles – 1996 Lone Star Film & Television Awards\nBULLET::::- Best Screenplay (Win) – John Sayles – 1996 Lone Star Film & Television Awards\nBULLET::::- Special Achievement Award for Outstanding Feature Film (Win) – 1996 NCLR Bravo Awards\nBULLET::::- Best Director (Win) – John Sayles – 1997 Southeastern Film Critics Association Awards\n\nAwards for \"The Secret of Roan Inish\":\nBULLET::::- Best Genre Video Release (Nominated) – 1996 Academy of Science Fiction, Fantasy & Horror Films\nBULLET::::- International Critics Award (Win) – John Sayles – 1996 Gérardmer Film Festival\nBULLET::::- Best Director (Nominated) – John Sayles – 1996 Independent Spirit Awards\nBULLET::::- Best Screenplay (Nominated) – John Sayles – 1996 Independent Spirit Awards\n\nAwards for \"Passion Fish\":\nBULLET::::- Best Original Screenplay (Nominated) – John Sayles – 1993 Academy Awards\nBULLET::::- Golden Spur Award (Win) – John Sayles – 1993 Flanders International Film Festival\nBULLET::::- Best Screenplay Written Directly for the Screen (Nom